N:task-planning
D:Turn vague features, bugs, roadmap items, launch work, or playtest findings into execution-ready planning packets with horizon choice, slice boundaries, dependencies, acceptance criteria, blockers, and one clear next move. Use when the user needs backlog grooming, sprint or milestone preparation, roadmap-to-delivery translation, or a practical "what should we actually do next?" planning pass across developer workflow, web/fullstack, product/ops, marketing/GTM, or game work. Route sizing to task-estimation, board control to vibe-kanban, plan review to plannotator, daily cadence to standup-meeting, and retros to sprint-retrospective.
G:task-planning backlog-grooming sprint-planning milestone-planning roadmap-slicing feature-breakdown launch-planning game-development
